{{copy edit|for=may be a translation|date=August 2012}}
'' 'Stimmhorn''' was a [[Swiss]] band. Their style could be described as experimental ethno-music, or [[Imaginary Folklore.]]

The band was formed in 1996 by Balthasar Streiff <ref> [http://www.streiffalphorn.ch/biografie/ short biography Balthasar Streiff] </ref> and [[Christian Zehnder]] <ref> [http:// www.zehndermusic.ch/cms/front_content.php?idcat=73 short biography Christian Zehnder] </ref> founded. The band's name referred to the music of the band, which consisted mainly of the voice of Christian Zehnder and Balthasar of different horn sounds Streiff. The instrumentation and technique of the band was very multifaceted. Christian Zehnder ruled alongside "normal" song also [[overtone]] [[yodel]] and plays the instruments [[Wippkordeon]], n [[bandoneon]] [[bandurria]] [[organ pipe]], [[Hang (musical instrument) | Hang]] and others. Balthasar Streiff plays, besides singing, the instruments [[alphorn]], double Alphorn, [[Alpofon]] (a system developed by his own instrument), [[B<U+00FC>chel (Musical instrument) | B<U+00FC>chel]] [[Cornet (instrument) | Cornet]] [[natural trumpet | Baroque trumpet]] [[zinc (music) | zinc]] [[tuba]] and [[horny goat]].

In addition, the duo often worked with guest musicians, such as the [[Overtone singing]] group [[Huun-Huur-Tu]] from [[Tuva]], such as on their album Igloo, and on a production of [[Faust]].


Zehnder and Streiff played in November 2009 for the last time as a duo "Stimmhorn" on. <ref> [Http://www.zehndermusic.ch/cms/front_content.php?idcat=89&idart=186 zehndermusic.ch] </ref>

== Awards ==

Their music helped the band to various national and international awards, including:

* 1997 First [[Swiss Kleinkunstpreis]], Prix de la sc<U+00E8>ne Suisse 1997
* 1997 [[Evening Newspaper | Z]] Star of the Year, for outstanding musical performance in Munich in 1997.
* 1998 [[Iron Eversteiner]] (European ethno-music award) Jury and Audience Award

== Discography ==

* Heimatkl<U+00E4>nge (Soundtrack, 2007)
* igloo (stimmhorn & kold electronics, 2004)
* inland (2001)
* schnee (1997)
* melken (1996)

